Model.Text: (Is it because the Martial Arts Tournament is coming? Seems like the medicine market is much busier than usual...)
So, I heard that turtle friend of yours came back from the Desert Kingdom... Or, wait, is he a tortoise?
Oh man, quit it with that, will ya? I'm sick of hearin' about it already!
Now are we s'posed to be the Turtle Tribe, or the Tortoise Tribe, or what!? Y'all 'spect us to do some DNA test or sumthin'?

(From the Desert Kingdom? Now I'm curious...
Ahh... no, I shouldn't get involved. Today I'm just here for supplies...)
Wait a second... something seems a little off about this guy's herbs.
Do ya' have any questions, miss? Need an explanation?
These sunflowers should be red... why are they pink?
Eh!? You accusin' me of sumthin'!?
I just might be. Here... look at them one way they seem red, but put them in the sun... they're pink!
If I remember correctly, only expired ones do that. Sure, it might be cheaper, but they're basically useless once they expire...
What? Why do you look so surprised?
Hmph! Figures sum' darn human's gonna barge right over and pitch a fit!
(Oh yeah, I'm not wearing my veil, and I changed my clothes...)

You humans just love to act like you know everything, like you're some kinda expert!
Well you better git, cause I got nuthin' to sell ya!
I don't want your fake medicine anyway!
Quit y'er' hollerin'! If you knew anything you'd know I've been here for decades, and I'm as honest a tortoise there is!
Then how about this maple incense?
Maple incense is supposed to smell like, you know, maple! This one looks the part, but it smells like plums!
Hah! That's ridiculous! Yer nose got problems is all.
And what about this autumn pine? it's all wilted! Don't you know it'll get ruined if you put it in water?
You about done yet!? I said git!
(This human is... impressive. But why do I feel like she looks familiar...?)
Hey, someone come help over here! Or y'all think it's okay if a human comes and disrespects us tortoises?
(Oh, crap!)
She's right. What you're doing is wrong—it's fraud.
Who are you?
Just a passerby who saw some injustice.
Get 'em, darn it!!
Now would be a very good time to leave!
O-Ok!
I think we're in the clear...
Thank you... you really got me out of a jam back there.
Don't thank me. People should help each other, right? And all those dirtbags that sell fake herbs should get what's coming to them, anyway.
Speaking of—you don't look like you're from around here. How do you know East Alliance herbs so well?
Actually, I am from aro—Ah! I mean...
It's because I have a really great teacher here. I came to the market to do some shopping for her.
Is that right? I'm actually studying here under a specific master as well. Or, I guess you could say we're old friends...
Anyway, since it seems like you're out of harm's way, I think it's time for me to get going.
That road there... it leads up to the Alliance Hall, right?
Yep. I'm going to try and sign up for the Martial Arts Tournament.
(Sign up? A human contestant?)
Uh... are you the current Panther Tribe champion, by chance? Miranda?
You've heard of me?
O-Of course! You're famous!
Famous? I don't think I've done anything fame-worthy...
Huh? A human in the Martial Arts Tournament is already special enough, let alone bringing back the panther's Holy Talisman.
(That's good... if people are paying attention to me, then they won't be paying attention to Master...)
But aren't you Master Law's student? Why don't you compete for the Wolf Tribe?
Hah~ you get straight to the point.
Oh, I'm sorry! My mom always tells me to watch what I say...
It's alright. It's best to be direct, I think. It's people who make assumptions and start rumors that I can't stand.
Anyway, it's because... Master Law's standing in the tribe isn't so great. They refused to give him the holy talisman.
(So the rumors are true?)
I'm sorry, I think I've asked a question I shouldn't have.
It's fine. I've got a talisman either way.
I have no idea why the Alliance keeps delaying sign-up, though.
Actually, while I was just coming over here,
I heard a soldier stationed in the contestant's quarters say that diplomats from the Sun and Desert Kingdoms were here to see the arbiter.
I hope that doesn't complicate things even more.
(The diplomats have arrived already!? If they're here for what it said in that letter, then... mom...)
(I've got to get back and see what's going on!)
Is something wrong? You got really pale all of a sudden...
I forgot, my teacher needs me to get back and put these herbs away as soon as possible.
Thank you for everything, Miss Miranda. I've got to be going!
